### 11762 CBIR: INSTRUCTIONS FOR SETTING UP THE DEVELOPMENT TOOLKIT

1. Install Anaconda (https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual) or Miniconda (https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html) for your operating system.

2. Unzip this zip file into a writable place of your operating system

3. Import the provided environment:

conda env create -f iric.yml

It includes, among other packages:
- Python 3.9.7
- Numpy
- Matplotlib
- SciPy
- SciKit-Learn 
- Pandas 
- Jupyter Notebooks
- OpenCV (including contrib) 4.5.5.62

4. Activate the environment:

conda activate iric

5. Download the INRIA Holidays datasets (normal and mini versions):

Holidays Mini:
https://uibes-my.sharepoint.com/:u:/g/personal/egf350_id_uib_eu/ESD-5xGCnm1Jsn-H9PDWN7ABL5U9Crx_De-eru3aATAFvQ

Holidays:
https://uibes-my.sharepoint.com/:u:/g/personal/egf350_id_uib_eu/Ef38Lm_85YRPs5E6JF2ffo8BrRrOMcwNbgD0FavzizZ6xw

These datasets should be then unzipped into the root directory of the development tookit.

6. Assignments should be also unzipped in the root directory of the development toolkit.

In summary, your development toolkit folder should look like this:
A1
A2
A3
...
holidays
holidays_mini
iric_utils
iric.yml
README

7. Go to the root directory of your development toolkit and then launch notebooks from there:

jupyter notebook

8. Develop each assignment following the particular instructions for each of them.

9. Submit your assigment as indicated.
